The paper deals with image restoration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus on human-centric machine learning and user satisfaction suggests a potential fit for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The iterative nature of the framework and the use of user feedback could also make it relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of image priors and the incorporation of human painting knowledge suggest a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
